report_text: The patient shows symptoms of fever, cough, and body ache.
Complaints of chest pain, shortness of breath, and fatigue.
Blurred vision and frequent urination observed.
MRI scan reveals brain lesions; signs of memory loss.
Skin rashes, joint pain, and positive ANA test.
X-ray shows swollen joints; reports morning stiffness.
Complaints include increased thirst and unhealed wounds.
Blood test shows high cholesterol and irregular heartbeat.
